page.title: 15COUNTESTHORPE FUNGI
page.content:
Around Countesthorpe High School, Jim Greany,a teacher, has found different kinds of fungi,from the edible Field Mushroom to the very poisonous fungi.
The edible ones have included the Horse Mushroom,the Prince Mushroom(Agaricus Augustus),the Agaric Bitorquis,the Shaggy Parasol,the Parasol Mushroom,the Field Blewit, Oyster Mushroom and the blackish purple Rassula(only edible if cooked). The Inkcaps,the poisonous ones,have included the Yellow Staining Mushroom, the Wooly Milkcap and the Grisset, which is not poisonous but can easily be confused with the Amanita Phalloides,the most poisonous fungi in the world.
